->google->Open Handset Alliance (OHA)
Dalvik Virtual Machine( DVM is like JVM ) optimized for mobile devices

activity -actions,view - seeing parts (button)
intent:
Start the service
Launch an activity
Display a web page
Display a list of contacts
Broadcast a message
Dial a phone call etc.
-------------------------
Intent intent=new Intent(Intent.ACTION_VIEW);  
intent.setData(Uri.parse("http://www.javatpoint.com"));  
startActivity(intent);  
---------------------------------
service-background process
Content Provider- share data between the applications
Fragment-display one or more fragments on the screen at the same time
Android Virtual Device (AVD)-emulate 
Activity <- FragmentActivity <- AppCompatActivity <- ActionBarActivity
R. it an autogenerated file and it contain id of all resource file(rec), id generated by Android Asset Packaging Tool , R is class name
--------------------------------------
Manifest file: It contains information about package including components such as activities, services, content providers etc.
<manifest> root element of the AndroidManifest.xml file
<application> subelements 
<intent-filter> type of intent to which activity, service or broadcast receiver can respond to
<action> action for the intent-filter
<category> It adds a category name to an intent-filter.
----------------------------------------
widget:
android.widget.Button subclass of TextView class
CompoundButton is the subclass of Button class
there is two ways we can perform with button by using setonclicklistner and onclick






